<node TEXT="List from XMind" ID="ID_1419870737" CREATED="1259737478706" MODIFIED="1262925174114" BOOKMARKS_UPDATED="0"><richcontent TYPE="NOTE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <h3>
      Meeting Organizers
    </h3>
    <ul class="h3-ul">
      <li>
        Use mind map or other charts to prepare the meeting details.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use hierarchy maps and shortcuts to capture meeting information.
      </li>
      <li>
        Record the meeting structurally, in real-time.
      </li>
      <li>
        Systematize and distribute the results.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>
      Project Managers
    </h3>
    <ul class="h3-ul">
      <li>
        Use mind map to list all the key points.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use Fishbone charts to make a project plan.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use Speadsheet to analyze all aspects of the project.
      </li>
      <li>
        Include all related information as hyperlinks or attachments.
      </li>
      <li>
        Filter topics during presentations or discussions.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>
      Teachers
    </h3>
    <ul class="h3-ul">
      <li>
        Use suitable structures for different scenarios to teach concepts.
      </li>
      <li>
        Drill down to sub-topics to show detailed information.
      </li>
      <li>
        Teach more effectively using a new presentation style.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use multi-maps, attachments and hyperlinks to show related knowledge.
      </li>
      <li>
        Filter the knowledge to show the key points or others concepts.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>
      Department Members
    </h3>
    <ul class="h3-ul">
      <li>
        Perform brainstorming and note the results.
      </li>
      <li>
        Assign responsibilities for each group project with different markers and/or label.
      </li>
      <li>
        Record audio notes of discussions.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>
      Students
    </h3>
    <ul class="h3-ul">
      <li>
        Set daily, weekly, monthly or yearly study plans.
      </li>
      <li>
        Note core knowledge points with multi-structures.
      </li>
      <li>
        Record key points as the attachments within maps.
      </li>
      <li>
        Track knowledge points as well-structured hierarchies within knowledge system.
      </li>
      <li>
        Conduct brainstorming sessions with classmates.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>
      Team Managers
    </h3>
    <ul class="h3-ul">
      <li>
        Plan work for all the members.
      </li>
      <li>
        Analyze work targets and schedules.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use multi-source to include all related information.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>
      Architects
    </h3>
    <ul class="h3-ul">
      <li>
        Use floating topics to instantly capture spontaneous flashes of creativity.
      </li>
      <li>
        Include related information as attachments or hyperlinks.
      </li>
      <li>
        Directly locate related images or text.
      </li>
      <li>
        Systematize all critical information.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>
      Designers
    </h3>
    <ul class="h3-ul">
      <li>
        Capture the flow of creative ideas without interruptions.
      </li>
      <li>
        Brainstorm alone, or with others, using floating topic capabilities.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use keyword search to obtain related information.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
